{
  "stem": "15017.1",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And my wife, when I walked in, she looked at me and she said, what's the matter with you?",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I said, hellzapoppin'.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Because at that time, there was a comedian in America that was doing a show called Hellzapoppin'.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I said hell-- and she started to laugh, you know.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But anyhow, I kept on working.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I was still at the Mirabell when I was called up.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I was called up to the 50th-- I was called up to the 57th Training Regiment, Royal Armoured-- Royal Tank Corps, which later became the Royal Armoured Corps.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[INTERPOSING VOICES] The draft was set up that every week in the newspaper it appeared that those born on so-and-so date, and so-and-so date, and so-and-so date register at the post office.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And when it came my time, I registered at the post office.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But they usually waited till a week after your birthday.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So I was called into the army on September the 18th, 1940.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "29.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I went through training, but when they found out that I was a professional musician and who I'd worked with, and what I did-- the band had suffered terribly in the evacuation of-- evacuation of Greece, at that time, when Greece fell, you know-- that most of the musicians that were in the band were stretcher bearers.",
      "word_count": 58
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And they had been taken prisoner.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So the band, the nucleus, had to be made up again.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I went straight from the drill, from being drilled, you know, on the barracks square, I went straight into the band, which is a very cushy job.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we had a band master, Reg Ridewood, his name was, an absolute gentleman.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And we did very well.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
